{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Checkbox is a UI element that allows to select multiple options from a set of mutually non exclusive choices."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Checkbox item covers a wider range of contexts by allowing to toggle the visibility of additional text labels and icon assets."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSCheckboxItem"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Layouts","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Layouts"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component can be rendered as two different layouts:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}]},{"type":"text","text":": the component has a leading indicator, a label and optional helper texts, and an optional trailing decorative icon"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"reversed"}]},{"type":"text","text":": like the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}]},{"type":"text","text":" layout but with a trailing checkbox indicator and a leading optional image"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Indicator-states","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Indicator states"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The checkbox indicator has three available states:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"selected"}]},{"type":"text","text":": the checkbox is filled with a tick, the user has made the action to select the checkbox"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"unselected"}]},{"type":"text","text":": the checkbox is empty, does not contain a tick, the user has made the action to unselect or did not select yet the checkbox"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you are looking for a checkbox component with three states, use instead "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Particular-cases","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Particular cases"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItem","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" can be related to an error situation, for example troubles for a formular."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A dedicated look and feel is implemented for that if the "},{"code":"isError","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" flag is risen."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In that case if the component displayed an icon, this icon will be replaced automatically by an error icon."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In addition, the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItem","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" can be in read only mode, i.e. the user cannot interact with the component yet but this component must not be considered"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as disabled."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component does not follow the right-to-left (RTL) \/ left-to-right (LTR) mode returned by the system as it could have some meaning"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to have for example the indicator in trailing position for LTR mode and vice versa."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, if the component has an icon in leading position (RTL mode) or in trailing position (LTR), the content of the icon is never changed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It could lead to a loss of meaning or semantics in the icon. Thus a specific flag can be used to flip the icon content whatever the layout direction is."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It prevents the user do implement its own rules to flip or not image."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Rich-text","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Rich text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Rich text can only be used for error messages."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Strong text can be used sparingly to highlight key information within the content."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"No other text styles should be used."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Underlined text must not be applied manually (e.g. in error message), as it is commonly associated with hyperlinks and may mislead users."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Accessibility considerations"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Always check the results of rich text mode with high contrast, light and dark modes, and Voice Over vocalization."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Voice Over"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" will use several elements to describe the component: if component disabled \/ read only, if error context, the label and helper texts and a custom checkbox trait."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"No accessibility identifier is defined in OUDS side as this value remains in the users hands."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Forbidden-by-design","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Forbidden by design"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a read only component."}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a disabled component."}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The design system does not allow to have both a read only and a disabled component."}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Code-samples","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Code samples"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Supposing we have an unselected checkbox","    @Published var isOn: Bool = false","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"Hello world\", isOn: $isOn)","","    \/\/ Localizable from bundle can also be used","    OUDSCheckboxItem(LocalizedStringKey(\"agree_terms\"), bundle: Bundle.module, isOn: $isOn)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label, but in read only mode (user cannot interact yet, but not disabled).","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"Hello world\", isOn: $isOn, isReadOnly: true)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label and a description as helper text.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"Bazinga!\", isOn: $isOn, description: \"Doll-Dagga Buzz-Buzz Ziggety-Zag\")","","    \/\/ A trailing checkbox with a label, a description and an icon.","    \/\/ The reversed layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"We live in a fabled world\",","                     isOn: $isOn,","                     description: \"Of dreaming boys and wide-eyed girls\",","                     isReversed: true,","                     icon: Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\"))","","    \/\/ If on error, add an error message can help user to understand error context","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"We live in a fabled world\",","                     isOn: $isOn,","                     isError: true,","                     errorText: \"Something wrong\",","                     hasDivider: true)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label, but disabled.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"Hello world\", isOn: $isOn)","        .disabled(true)","","    \/\/ Never disable a read only or an error-related checkbox as it will crash","    \/\/ This is forbidden by design!","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"Hello world\", isOn: $isOn, isError: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"Hello world\", isOn: $isOn, isReadOnly: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need to flip your icon depending to the layout direction or not (e.g. if RTL mode lose semantics  \/ meanings):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"Cocorico !\",","                     isOn: $selection,","                     icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","                     flipIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft,","                     isInversed: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Suggestions","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Suggestions"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"According to the "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-checkbox","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the checkbox by default must be used in unselected state."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Design documentation"},{"inlineContent":[{"overridingTitle":"unified-design-system.orange.com","identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-checkbox","type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"unified-design-system.orange.com"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Themes-rendering","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Themes rendering"},{"anchor":"Orange","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Orange"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_checkboxItem_Orange","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Orange-Compact","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Orange Compact"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_checkboxItem_OrangeCompact","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Sosh","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Sosh"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_checkboxItem_Sosh","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Wireframe","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Wireframe"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_checkboxItem_Wireframe","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"2.4.0 (Figma component design version)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Version"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.12.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Since"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"type":"conformsTo"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItem","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSCheckboxItem"}],"platforms":[{"unavailable":false,"name":"iOS","beta":false,"deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"15.0"},{"unavailable":false,"name":"macOS","beta":false,"d